{"agent_id":"claude","agent_seq":12,"timestamp":"2026-06-21T00:28:11.486507823Z","event":{"type":"IssueCreated","uuid":"9c0a1105-e085-41b6-96e8-1fd958fde773","title":"Address Copilot review on PR #1184","description":"Steps to reproduce:\n1. \n\nExpected: \nActual: \n\nPR: fix(test): make test_cache_hits_recorded deterministic with explicit tolerated ranges\nhttps://github.com/openwpm/OpenWPM/pull/1184\n\n## Unresolved Copilot review threads\n\n- `test/test_http_instrumentation.py:None` [outdated]\n\n  `allowed_request_urls` is built with the `|` operator against `CACHE_DEPENDENT_REQUEST_URL_RANGES.keys()`. This relies on `dict_keys` set-op behavior (and can also trip static type checkers like mypy/pyright with “unsupported operand types” for `set[str] | dict_keys[str]`). Using `set.union()` (or wrapping the keys in `set(...)`) is clearer and avoids potential CI type-check failures.\n\n---\n\nVERIFY each claim before acting — Copilot is fallible (it once flagged a valid os.getenv(key, default=...) as a bug). If real -> fix + resolve the thread. If wrong -> post a reasoned rebuttal + resolve. Builder -> the-hater -> done; never blindly apply.","priority":"high","created_by":"claude","display_id":61},"signed_by":"SHA256:s7/xSWzYQxlilryCkQ+87ei/Tb4h7UF7S3hGGeMOxBg","signature":"U1NIU0lHAAAAAQAAADMAAAALc3NoLWVkMjU1MTkAAAAgxYoY2+ykEqIdJITiF+QWTxSzAQrzXLyHaApd+5sgGJAAAAAPY3Jvc3NsaW5rLWV2ZW50AAAAAAAAAAZzaGE1MTIAAABTAAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAQG+d2kA2GmWmahJOdPnclkegNIrtgcP/Rxu61SiWqcIfjSx6tdQAHQroCq1bPoGkOjRf6fFHBUDfOSOKxbzb/AE="}
