{"agent_id":"claude","agent_seq":27,"timestamp":"2026-06-21T00:28:40.905293927Z","event":{"type":"IssueCreated","uuid":"dc240677-75b4-49fe-89fb-acb705da5343","title":"Address Copilot review on PR #1155","description":"Steps to reproduce:\n1. \n\nExpected: \nActual: \n\nPR: feat(ci): dynamic test duration tracking for pytest-split\nhttps://github.com/openwpm/OpenWPM/pull/1155\n\n## Unresolved Copilot review threads\n\n- `test/conftest.py:32`\n\n  `GROUP` is used directly to construct an output filename. Even though this is intended for CI, it’s still an environment-provided string and can contain path separators (e.g., `../`) or other unexpected characters that redirect writes outside the repo. Consider sanitizing `group` to an allowed set (e.g., digits only or a conservative regex like `^[A-Za-z0-9_-]+$`) before using it in the filename; otherwise skip writing and/or log a brief warning.\n\n- `.github/workflows/run-tests.yaml:44`\n\n  The restore key hard-codes `refs/heads/master`, but the repo appears to use `main` (diff base shows `index main..branch`). This will prevent cache reuse on the default branch if it’s actually `main`. Prefer using the default branch dynamically (e.g., `github.event.repository.default_branch`) or update the fallback to `refs/heads/main-`.\n  ```suggestion\n              test-durations-refs/heads/${{ github.event.repository.default_branch }}-\n  ```\n\n---\n\nVERIFY each claim before acting — Copilot is fallible (it once flagged a valid os.getenv(key, default=...) as a bug). If real -> fix + resolve the thread. If wrong -> post a reasoned rebuttal + resolve. Builder -> the-hater -> done; never blindly apply.","priority":"high","created_by":"claude","display_id":66},"signed_by":"SHA256:s7/xSWzYQxlilryCkQ+87ei/Tb4h7UF7S3hGGeMOxBg","signature":"U1NIU0lHAAAAAQAAADMAAAALc3NoLWVkMjU1MTkAAAAgxYoY2+ykEqIdJITiF+QWTxSzAQrzXLyHaApd+5sgGJAAAAAPY3Jvc3NsaW5rLWV2ZW50AAAAAAAAAAZzaGE1MTIAAABTAAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAQJWG+W+zkGAhKpS6LJt4JrhLyE65vYIRgg0OZaPY